# Find returns in single paragraph

This is a handy GREP for InDesign for using when copying plain text into a document that has returns in a paragraph that you want rid of. BUT it will only check a paragraph and not remove the returns separating the paragraph if there is no Space After set for the paragraph.

(?<!~b)~b(?!~b)

Originally found in the comments here: https://indesignsecrets.com/remove-multiple-returns-and-replace-with-space-between-paragraphs.php
